President Uhuru Kenyatta Today Hosted Nairobi County Jubilee Party MCAs At State House To Discuss The Leadership Crisis Bedeviling The County. The Crisis Had Crippled Service Delivery Prompting The National Government To Take Over Four Critical Functions Of The Devolved Unit. During The Meeting, The Issue Of National Unity And The Intensified Fight Against Corruption Took Centre Stage      With The President Assuring The MCA’s Nobody Will Be Spared And That There Will Be No Sacred Cows. The State House Meeting Took Place As The County Assembly Readies Itself For A Three Marathon Session From Tuesday Until Thursday To Discuss An Impeachment Motion That Has Been Filed By Minority Leader Peter Imwatok.